    ComponentDependent, ModelDependent, IntrospectingEditor, java.awt.datatransfer.ClipboardOwner, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.beans.PropertyEditor, java.io.Serializable, javax.accessibility.Accessible
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OptionalCDoubleEditor
    public class CDoubleEditor
extends javax.swing.JPanel
implements IntrospectingEditor, java.awt.datatransfer.ClipboardOwner, ComponentDependent
    An editor a double that appears to the user to be a dimensionless CReal. Methods can be overridden to provide units information.
    See Also:
    getConversionFactor(), getConversionOffset(), getENG_Units(), getSI_Units(), Serialized Form

      • generateFormat

        public java.text.DecimalFormat generateFormat​(double value,
                                              int maxColumns)
        Creates a new DecimalFormat to format the given d within the given maximum number of columns. The given number of columns is assumed to be for a positive d. 1 will be subtracted from this number if d is < 0.0.
        Parameters:
        value - the double to create a format for
        maxColumns - the maximum number of columns that d can occupy if it is positive.
        Returns:
        a DecimalFormat with a custom generated format for the given d
